According to Table 3, none of the analyzed PAH species is related to TPH. By implementing the backward GEE model, it was indicated that the Nap, Chr, BbF and Ind have the greatest effect on TPH (Table 4
). For more accuracy, the backward GEE model was also implemented on Nap, Chr, BbF and Ind group against TPH (Table 5
). The results revealed Ind effect on the TPH levels as Ind is a six-ring HMW PAH with the molecular weight of 276. Thus, Ind is more stable in the environment and usually makes a fraction of TPH concentration; however, it does not necessarily mean that the rest of PAH species are ineffective.
